            About me
            I am an international development professional. Fluent in Spanish and English and a “third culture kid”. I was born in Ecuador and have lived in ten countries: Ecuador, Tanzania, USA, Guatemala, Honduras, Ghana, Italy, Australia, Dominican Republic, United Kingdom (Master’s degree), and now back in Ecuador. I studied International Studies and Management at Pepperdine University and attained a master’s degree in Development Studies at the London School of Economics and Political Science. I currently work for an international development non-profit in Quito, Ecuador.
            
            
            Education
            London School of Economics and Political Science | London, UK
            MSc in Development Studies | September 2018 - Aug 2019
            Pepperdine University | Malibu, California, USA
            BA in International Studies and Management | September 2005 - May 2009
            Minor in Non-profit Management
            
            
            Experience
            Endeavor | Entrepreneur Selection and Growth Associate | March 2020 - Present
            PwC | Operations Consultant Associate | September 2019 - February 2020
            Yspaniola Inc | Princeton in Latin America Fellow | Sept 2017-April 2018
